{{italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Eubacterium nodatum'' | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Firmicutes]] | classis = [[Clostridia]] | ordo = [[Clostridia]]le | familia = [[Eubacteriaceae]] | genus = ''[[Eubacterium]]'' | species = '''''E. nodatum''''' | binomial = '''''Eubacterium nodatum''''' | binomial_authority = [[Lillian V. Holdeman|Holdeman]] et al. 1980 }}
'''''Eubacterium nodatum''''' is a [[Gram positive]] member of the [[oral flora]] of some patients with [[chronic periodontitis]].<ref>AAP In-Service Exam, 2008-B37</ref> It has been recently added to the red complex bacteria, that are most associated with disease.
