{{no footnotes|date=March 2016}}
The '''NICO Clean Tobacco Card''' was a device exported from [[Japan]] to the [[United States]] in the 1960s, consisting of a small card impregnated with [[Uraninite|uranium ore]].  The card was to be placed inside a pack of [[cigarette]]s, and the producers claimed that the [[radiation]] emitted by the card would reduce [[tar]] and [[nicotine]], and enhance the [[smoking]] experience.

A similar product, the Nicotine Alkaloid Control Plate, was produced in the 1990s but not exported.

